Anyone with an index of 30 or higher is considered obese.
The health effects of obesity have been staggering.
Obesity contributes to over 300,000 excess deaths each year.
For obese people weight loss is essential.
The disease is most often seen in people over age 45 who are overweight.
A national survey conducted by the Diabetic Association of Pakistan (DAP) reveals that there are now some 4.3 million diabetics in Pakistan and the figure is likely to reach 14.5 million by 2025.
First, obesity must be recognized as the serious public health problem.
